# .gitignore - Supreme Code Evolution Controller Configuration
# Version: DARLEK CANN v3.0
# Purpose: This file specifies intentionally untracked files and directories that Git should ignore.
# It ensures a clean repository, prevents accidental commits of sensitive data, build artifacts,
# temporary files, and user-specific configurations, aligning with robust CI/CD pipelines and
# collaborative development practices across the DARLEK CANN ecosystem.

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. NODE.JS / NPM / YARN / PNPM - Package Manager Artifacts & Dependencies
#    Architectural Blueprint: Prevents inclusion of installed dependencies and package manager caches.
#    Technical Workflow: Essential for clean builds and consistent environments, as node_modules
#    should be generated from package-lock.json/yarn.lock/pnpm-lock.yaml.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
node_modules/
.npm/
.yarn/
.pnpm-store/

# Package manager debug logs
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
lerna-debug.log*

# Yarn Plug'n'Play (PnP) files
.pnp/
.pnp.js

# Compressed packages
*.tgz

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. BUILD ARTIFACTS - Compiled Output & Transpiled Files
#    Architectural Blueprint: Defines standard output directories for compilation and bundling.
#    Technical Workflow: These directories are generated during the build process and should not
#    be version controlled. They are derived from source code.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
build/
dist/
out/
coverage/

# TypeScript specific build artifacts (inferred from user's TypeScript-heavy portfolio)
*.tsbuildinfo
*.js.map
*.d.ts.map

# Common temporary build directories
tmp/
temp/

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. NEXT.JS SPECIFIC - Framework-Generated Files (Siphoned from 'darlek-cann-v3')
#    Architectural Blueprint: Specific directories and files generated by the Next.js framework.
#    Technical Workflow: These are internal Next.js caches and build outputs that are recreated
#    on demand and are not part of the source code.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.next/

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES - Sensitive Configuration & Local Overrides
#    Architectural Blueprint: Critical for security and environment-specific configurations.
#    Technical Workflow: Prevents sensitive API keys, database credentials, and local development
#    settings from being committed to the repository. `!.env.example` is explicitly kept for documentation.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.development.local
.env.test.local
.env.production.local

# Keep example environment file for reference
!.env.example

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. OPERATING SYSTEM SPECIFIC - OS-Generated Files
#    Architectural Blueprint: Standard ignores for files created by various operating systems.
#    Technical Workflow: These files are irrelevant to the project's source code and can cause
#    unnecessary noise in version control.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 6. IDE / EDITOR SPECIFIC - Integrated Development Environment Files
#    Architectural Blueprint: Ignores user-specific IDE settings or temporary files.
#    Technical Workflow: Ensures consistent development environments across teams by ignoring
#    personal preferences or transient editor data.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VS Code (common for TypeScript projects)
.vscode/*.local
.vscode/.history/

# Other common editor temporary files
*~
*.swp
*.swo
*.bak
*.orig

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 7. LOGS & DEBUGGING - Runtime Logs and Diagnostic Outputs
#    Architectural Blueprint: Defines patterns for various log files.
#    Technical Workflow: Log files are runtime outputs and should not be version controlled.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.log
*.log.*
debug.log

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 8. GENERATED FILES / DATA ARTIFACTS - AI/Simulation Outputs & Temporary Data
#    Architectural Blueprint: Critical for projects involving AI, simulations, or data processing
#    (siphoned from 'epistemic_debate_engine', 'nbody_gravitational_simulator', 'SN', 'unitary-core').
#    Technical Workflow: Prevents large datasets, model checkpoints, temporary processing outputs,
#    or local database files from being committed, which are often large, volatile, or sensitive.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Machine Learning Models / Checkpoints
models/*.pth
models/*.pt
models/*.h5
models/*.onnx
checkpoints/

# Simulation / Data Processing Outputs
output/
data/*.tmp
*.sqlite
*.db
*.csv.tmp
*.json.tmp

# User uploads or temporary storage
uploads/

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 9. TESTING & COVERAGE - Test Reports and Coverage Data
#    Architectural Blueprint: Standard ignores for test execution artifacts.
#    Technical Workflow: These files are generated during test runs and are not part of the source.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.nyc_output/
junit.xml
test-results.xml
*.tap



